      "content": "thanks. so when historians talk about those \"limitations\" or failures, is it usually because they think the UN system itself is broken or just because the countries involved wouldn't cooperate? like, is the consensus more that the institution is fundamentally flawed for our era, or just that the politics were too messy?",
